article.description: — Jake Wojcik posted 17 points to lead Fairfield past Marist 69-66 on Sunday.
article.headline: Wojcik scores 17 to lift Fairfield past Marist 69-66
article.linkText: Wojcik scores 17 to lift Fairfield past Marist 69-66
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. -- — Jake Wojcik posted 17 points to lead Fairfield past Marist 69-66 on Sunday. Taj Benning had 16 points for the Stags (9-10, 3-5 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference), who snapped a seven-game losing streak. Supreme Cook added 13 points and nine rebounds. Ricardo Wright had 19 points for the Red Foxes (8-9, 3-5). Samkelo Cele added 16 points. The Stags evened the season series against the Red Foxes. Marist defeated Fairfield 60-51 on Jan. 7. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ Portions of this story were generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
